{{BLP self-published|date=December 2012}} '''Brian D'Amato''' is an American author and sculptor.
==Biography== D'Amato received a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] from [[Yale University]] and an [[Masters Degree#MA.2C MS.2C MSc.2C MSE.2C AM.2C SM|MA]] from the [[CUNY Graduate Center]] <ref>[https://www.mlive.com/living/grand-rapids/index.ssf/2009/05/profile_artist_and_author_dria.html Article in "Profile: Artist and author Brian D'amato is a man of many talents"]</ref>. At Yale, D'Amato studied with [[John Hollander]], [[Erwin Hauer]], and William Bailey. At the Graduate Center of the City University of New York, he studied with [[Robert Pincus-Witten]].
In the 1990s, D’Amato showed sculptures and installations at galleries and museums including the [[Whitney Museum]], the [[Wexner Center for the Arts]] <ref>[https://wexarts.org/artist-residency/softworlds-janine-cirincione-brian-damato-and-michael-ferraro Article in "Softworlds (Janine Cirincione, Brian D'Amato, and Michael Ferraro)"]</ref>, and the [[New Museum of Contemporary Art]] <ref>[https://www.newmuseum.org/exhibitions/view/occupied-territory-a-new-museum-trilogy Article in "Occupied Territory: A New Museum Trilogy"]</ref>. He has written for magazines, including ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Index Magazine]]'', ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Flash Art]]'', and ''[[Artforum]]'', and he has taught art and art history at the [[City University of New York]], [[The Ohio State University]], and [[Yale University]].<ref name="cm">Chris Morgan, "D'Amato, Brian", [[David Pringle]], ''St. James Guide to Horror, Ghost & Gothic Writers''. London : St. James Press, 1998, {{ISBN|1558622063}} (pp 165-166).</ref>
D'Amato's 1992 novel, ''Beauty,'' a thriller (with [[Horror fiction|horror]] elements) about cosmetic surgery, was translated into several languages.<ref name="cm" /><ref>{{ISBN|9780385306768}}</ref> His next novel, titled ''In the Courts of the Sun'', is the first book of ''The Sacrifice Game'' trilogy and was published by [[Dutton Penguin|Dutton]] in 2009.<ref>[https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/6252/brian-damato "Penguin Random House: Authors"]</ref> [[New American Library]] published a trade paperback edition in 2009. The second book in the trilogy, ''The Sacrifice Game'', was published by [[Dutton Penguin|Dutton]] 2012.<ref>{{ISBN|9780525952411}}</ref> Beauty is being republished by [[Little, Brown and Company]]'s Mulholland Classics line in 2013.<ref>{{ISBN|9780316217248}}</ref> D'Amato's work is often associated with the genres of [[Biopunk]], [[Transhumanism in fiction]], and [[Posthumanism]]. D'Amato is the son of [[Northwestern University School of Law|Northwestern Law]] professor Anthony D'Amato and mystery novelist [[Barbara D'Amato]]<ref>[https://www.mlive.com/living/grand-rapids/index.ssf/2009/05/profile_artist_and_author_dria.html Article in "Profile: Artist and author Brian D'amato is a man of many talents"]</ref>.
